<div class="quotetitle">arfink wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />I have heard of the 29F256 being directly compatible (no rewiring) , but I really don't know. I have 27C256 chips and those work without having to be rewired in the socket.<br /></div><br />I use AT29C256's (256 kbits = 32 kbytes) without any rewiring. I also got some W27E512 (these are not Flash, they are eletrically erasable) that work without rewiring, even though they are 512 kbits (64 kbytes).<br /><br />I believe there are two kinds of NROM boards, NROM-128 and NROM-256, and the 128 kind can not read 256kbit chips. Well, it probably CAN read, but not all of it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Wed May 03, 2006 12:14 pm</p><hr />
