<div class="quotetitle">arfink wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />My programmer probably does not support flash at all.<br /></div><br /><br />It'd be worth finding out, on xeltec's site.  If it can write SRAM, it should be able to write flashrom too (hardware-wise at least, I dunno about the firmware/software).  Look up chips like AMD 29F040, or Atmel ones like 29C256 and 29C040.<br /><br />There are SRAM chips you can get with the battery built-in.  Lots of ones made by Dallas, I can't remember the part #s though.  But they look expensive and physically huge (nothing's really gonna fit in an NES cart case with a socket though anyways).  I see them on ebay a lot but don't know if I'd recommend using those.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Sun Apr 30, 2006 6:26 am</p><hr />
